stories.title: Pakistan v India
stories.subTitle: Second One-Day International
stories.summary: Once again, the hunters fell tantalisingly short in a high-scoring thriller, with India just failing after needing 16 off the last two overs.

stories.title: 'It was not an easy wicket to bat on'

stories.summary: It is a measure of the times that India could be deemed to have done well to have restricted Pakistan to 329

stories.title: Pakistan win despite Tendulkar's ton
stories.subTitle: Pakistan v India, 2nd ODI, Rawalpindi
stories.summary: Sachin Tendulkar carved a dazzling 141, but it wasn't enough to inspire India to an improbable victory after they were all out for 317, just 12 runs short
stories.byline: The Wisden Bulletin by Dileep Premachandran
